705183,"age":46,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705184,"age":56,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705185,"age":66,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Eudes DE BLOIS was born in 1040, in Blois 2e Canton, Blois, Loir-et-Cher, Centre, France, his father, Étienne II comte de Troyes et de Meaux, was 25 and his mother, Adèle d'Aumale, was 20. He married Adelaide de Normandie about 1060. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He registered for military service in 1066."},"et":{"1040–1115":"1040–1115","1036–1085":"1036–1085","1045–1118":"1045–1118","1029–1082":"1029–1082","1061–1127":"1061–1127","1015–1048":"1015–1048","1020–1090":"1020–1090","about 1061":"umbes 1061","about 1060":"umbes 1060","1090":"1090","1066":"1066","1088":"1088","1086":"1086","1020":"1020","1096":"1096","1085":"1085","1040":"1040","1061":"1061","1082":"1082","19 May 1048":"19. mai 1048","1118":"1118","1106":"1106","1029":"1029","1127":"1127","1115":"1115","1048":"1048","1015":"1015","1036":"1036","1045":"1045","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","England":"Ingl